# Code Style

## Universal
- Never use em dashes anywhere in code, comments, or docstrings
- Type hints required on every function signature, no bare dict or Any
- Descriptive variable names, no single letter variables except loop counters
- Functions stay small and single-purpose, split if doing more than one thing
- Files stay under 300 lines, split into smaller modules if exceeded
- Inline comments explain why, not what
- Every service function must have a docstring

## Python
- Pydantic v2 syntax only
  - Use model_validator and field_validator, never the old @validator
  - Use model_config = ConfigDict(...) never inner class Config
- f-strings for all string formatting, never .format() or %
- Pathlib for all file paths, never os.path string concatenation
- asyncio.to_thread() for any blocking calls inside async functions
- Import order: stdlib, third-party, local, separated by blank lines

## Git commit format
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- refactor: restructuring without behavior change
- chore: tooling, config, dependencies
- Commit after every meaningful unit of work
- Never commit .env, __pycache__, or secrets

## Never do
- Never use pip, always uv
- Never hardcode values that belong in config
- Never use sync calls inside async functions
- Never use Pydantic v1 syntax
- Never use bare except clauses
- Never return raw exceptions to the client
- Never commit API keys or secrets